1- To hide a file: "attrib +s +h (file name)"
   To display a hidden file: "attrib -s -h (file name)"
   
2- To create multiple nested directories with one mkdir command: "mkdir -p file1/file2/file3/......."

3- Execute following commands terminal:
   echo "test" > fun
   echo "another test" >> fun
   wc -c fun
   
   The result is : 18 fun
   
4- To get the output "testanother test", the command will be:
   echo -n "testanother" > fun
   echo "test" >> fun
   cat fun
   testanother test
   
----------------------------------------------------------------------------------   

The commands:

Zaed Magzoub@LAPTOP-VQ6AQFLO MINGW64 ~
$ pwd
/c/Users/acer

Zaed Magzoub@LAPTOP-VQ6AQFLO MINGW64 ~
$ mkdir zaed

Zaed Magzoub@LAPTOP-VQ6AQFLO MINGW64 ~
$ attrib +s +h zaed

Zaed Magzoub@LAPTOP-VQ6AQFLO MINGW64 ~
$ attrib -s -h zaed

Zaed Magzoub@LAPTOP-VQ6AQFLO MINGW64 ~
$ mkdir -p zaed1/zaed2/zaed3/zaed4

Zaed Magzoub@LAPTOP-VQ6AQFLO MINGW64 ~
$ echo "test" > fun

Zaed Magzoub@LAPTOP-VQ6AQFLO MINGW64 ~
$ echo "another test" >> fun

Zaed Magzoub@LAPTOP-VQ6AQFLO MINGW64 ~
$ wc -c fun
18 fun

Zaed Magzoub@LAPTOP-VQ6AQFLO MINGW64 ~
$ echo "testanother test" > fun

Zaed Magzoub@LAPTOP-VQ6AQFLO MINGW64 ~
$ cat fun
testanother test
